    {
      "parameters": {
        "promptType": "define",
        "text": "=Indicator JSON:\n\n{{ JSON.stringify($json) }}\n\nConversion Rules:\n\n1. pulse_count = pulse_info.count\n\n2. malware_count = count unique malware families across:\n   pulse_info.related.alienvault.malware_families\n   pulse_info.related.other.malware_families\n\n3. confidence_score =\n   pulse_count * 20 + malware_count * 30\n   Cap at 100.\n   If false_positive exists or validation contains \"whitelist\" or \"false positive\",\n   set confidence_score = 0.\n\n4. is_tor =\n   1 if validation contains any TOR-related flag,\n   otherwise 0.\n\n5. country_risk =\n   default 0.5\n   0.2 if whitelisted or false positive\n   0.8 if country_code in [RU, IR, KP, CN]\n\n6. asn_reputation =\n   use top-level reputation field\n   if missing, default 0.5\n\nReturn only the final feature dictionary as JSON.\nDo not include markdown formatting.",
        "messages": {
          "messageValues": [
            {
              "message": "=Role / System Prompt  You are a security data transformation engine. Your job is to convert raw threat-intelligence indicator JSON into a normalized, ML-ready feature dictionary compatible with the following schema:  {   \"pulse_count\": number,   \"malware_count\": number,   \"confidence_score\": number (0–100),   \"is_tor\": 0 or 1,   \"country_risk\": number (0–1),   \"asn_reputation\": number (0–1) }   Do not add explanations, comments, or extra fields. Output only valid JSON."
            }
          ]
        },
        "batching": {}
